"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-04-10-2024-summer-olympics-track-and-field-prize-money\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"For the first time, some winners at this summer's Olympics in Paris will take home more than a gold medal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 67, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999961354935388, \"rank\": 3.8645214256315386e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics, the governing body for track and field,announced Wednesdaythat it has established a prize fund of $2.4 million that will be used to award $50,000 to the gold medalists in each of the 48 athletics events scheduled for the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 108, \"end\": 123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 370, \"end\": 375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999961354935388, \"rank\": 3.8645214256315386e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It marks the first time that prize money has been offered to Olympians by a sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s governing body.\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many countries and national Olympic committees offer payments to medalists, but World Athletics will be the first federation to reward winners with cash prizes.\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Committee, for example, paid $37,500 to gold medalists at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021,according to the Associated Press.\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999833274455974, \"rank\": 1.4668989113757963e-05, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While only gold medalists will receive payouts this year, World Athletics announced a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cfirm commitment\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d to offer prizes to silver and bronze medalists at the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 852, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999985001688735, \"rank\": 1.4196907171438156e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhile it is impossible to put a marketable value on winning an Olympic medal, or on the commitment and focus it takes to even represent your country at an Olympic Games, I think it is important we start somewhere and make sure some of the revenues generated by our athletes at the Olympic Games are directly returned to those who make the Games the global spectacle that it is,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d World Athletics president Sebastian Coe said in a statement.\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1371, \"end\": 1386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1397, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The prize money will come from the revenue sharing funds that World Athletics receives from the International Olympic Committee every four years.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1495, \"end\": 1510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999999996437964, \"rank\": 3.5619731660201927e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medalists in individual events will receive the full $50,000, while winners in relay events will split the money.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Dan Gartland writes Sports Illustrated\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s flagship daily newsletter, SI:AM, and is the host of the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cStadium Wonders\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d video series.\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1794, \"end\": 1802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"score\": 0.9999996835124921, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gartland\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joined the SI staff in 2014, having previously been published on Deadspin and Slate.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 2013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gartland, a graduate of Fordham University, is a former Sports Jeopardy!\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2038, \"end\": 2056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fordham_University\", \"score\": 0.9999996299928401, \"rank\": 3.698135622281657e-07, \"text\": \"Fordham University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fordham_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fordham_University\"}, {\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Jeopardy!\", \"score\": 0.999999999927013, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sports Jeopardy!\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Jeopardy!\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Jeopardy!\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"champion (Season 1, Episode 5).\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands.\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2425, \"end\": 2443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.478863963720036e-14, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2714, \"entities\": []}]}"